<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><regulation id="LMS1583205" year.imprint="2026" date.as.at="2026-04-07" date.first.valid="2026-07-01" gazette-only="no" imperial="no" date.gazetted="2026-04-09" date.signed="2026-04-07" sr.no="84" year="2026" series="secondary-legislation" date.terminated="nulldate" sr.type="order"><cover id="LMS1583206"><title>Rates Rebate (Specified Amounts) Order 2026</title><gg>Cindy Kiro, Governor-General</gg><made><heading>Order in Council</heading><made.at>At Wellington this 7th day of April 2026</made.at><made.present>Present:<brk/>Her Excellency the Governor-General in Council</made.present></made></cover><front id="LMS1583207"><pursuant><para><text>This order is made under <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM409673" id="LMS1583237">section 3(2)</extref> of the <leg-title href="DLM409295" id="LMS1583238">Rates Rebate Act 1973</leg-title></citation> on the advice and with the consent of the Executive Council.</text></para></pursuant></front><contents><heading>Contents</heading><toc/></contents><body id="LMS1583214" prov-type="clause"><heading>Order</heading><prov id="LMS1583208" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">1</label><heading>Title</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>This order is the Rates Rebate (Specified Amounts) Order 2026.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1583209" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">2</label><heading>Commencement</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>This order comes into force on 1 July 2026.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1583210" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">3</label><heading>Principal Act</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text><citation jurisdiction="nz"><intref href="LMS1583211" id="LMS1583239">Clause 4</intref></citation> amends the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM409295" id="LMS1583217">Rates Rebate Act 1973</leg-title></citation>.</text></para></subprov></prov.body><notes><amends-note><amends-effective><date>2026-07-01</date></amends-effective><amends-affect><citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM409295" id="LMS1588742">Rates Rebate Act 1973</leg-title></citation></amends-affect></amends-note></notes></prov><prov id="LMS1583211" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">4</label><heading>Section 3 amended (Rates rebate)</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes">1</label><para><text>In <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM409673" id="LMS1583240">section 3(1)﻿(b)</extref></citation>, replace <amend.in>$805</amend.in> with <amend.in>$830</amend.in>.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">2</label><para><text>In <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM409673" id="LMS1583241">section 3(1AA)﻿(a)</extref></citation>, replace <amend.in>$45,000</amend.in> with <amend.in>$46,400</amend.in>.</text></para></subprov><subprov><label denominator="yes">3</label><para><text>In <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM409673" id="LMS1583242">section 3(1AA)﻿(b)</extref></citation>, replace <amend.in>$32,210</amend.in> with <amend.in>$33,210</amend.in>.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov><prov id="LMS1583212" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">5</label><heading>Revocation</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>The <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="LMS1033938" id="LMS1583243">Rates Rebate (Specified Amounts) Order 2025</leg-title></citation> (SL 2025/63) is revoked.</text></para></subprov></prov.body><notes><amends-note><amends-effective><date>2026-07-01</date></amends-effective><amends-affect><citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="LMS1033938" id="LMS1588743">Rates Rebate (Specified Amounts) Order 2025</leg-title></citation></amends-affect></amends-note></notes></prov><prov id="LMS1583213" toc="yes"><label denominator="yes">6</label><heading>Saving</heading><prov.body><subprov><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>A ratepayer’s entitlement to a rebate for a rating year ending before 1 July 2026, and the amount (if any) of that rebate, must be determined as if this order had not been made.</text></para></subprov></prov.body></prov></body><end id="LMS1583216"><signature-block><sig.para align="right">Rachel Hayward,<brk/>Clerk of the Executive Council.</sig.para></signature-block><explnote id="LMS1583215" rule-after="yes" rule-before="yes" series="statutory-regulation" date.as.at="2026-04-07" date.first.valid="2026-07-01" gazette-only="no" imperial="no" date.gazetted="2026-04-09" date.signed="2026-04-07" sr.no="84" year="2026" date.terminated="nulldate" sr.type="order"><heading>Explanatory note</heading><explnote.subhead2>This note is not part of the order but is intended to indicate its general effect.</explnote.subhead2><para><text>This order, which comes into force on 1 July 2026, amends <citation jurisdiction="nz"><extref href="DLM409673" id="LMS1583244">section 3(1) and (1AA) of the Rates Rebate Act 1973</extref></citation>. That section provides for a rates rebate for low-income home owners.</text></para><para><text>This order—</text><list><item><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>increases the maximum rates rebate from $805 to $830; and</text></para></item><item><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>increases the income threshold in relation to a rates rebate,—</text><list><item><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>for a ratepayer who holds a SuperGold Card, from $45,000 to $46,400; and</text></para></item><item><label denominator="yes"/><para><text>for any other ratepayer, from $32,210 to $33,210.</text></para></item></list></para></item></list></para></explnote><promulgation><issue-authority>Issued under the authority of the <citation jurisdiction="nz"><leg-title href="DLM7298104" id="LMS1583218">Legislation Act 2019</leg-title></citation>.</issue-authority><gazette-date>Date of notification in <emphasis style="italic">Gazette</emphasis>: 9 April 2026.</gazette-date><admin-office>This order is administered by the <ministry>Department of Internal Affairs</ministry>.</admin-office></promulgation></end></regulation>